cs.CR, cs.DC, cs.SE, cs.AR, cs.SY

Reasoning: 
- cs.CR (Cryptography and Security) is the most likely category as the paper focuses on privacy-preserving techniques and security protection.
- cs.DC (Distributed, Parallel, and Cluster Computing) is also likely as the paper discusses computing tasks on servers and the use of accelerators like GPU and TPU.
- cs.SE (Software Engineering) is a possibility as the paper presents a new design for a Trusted Execution Environment (TEE) and discusses the programming model.
- cs.AR (Hardware Architecture) is a possibility as the paper mentions the implementation of the HETEE design on a hardware prototype system.
- cs.SY (Systems and Control) is a possibility as the paper discusses the dynamic adjustment of the boundary between secure and insecure worlds through the PCIe switches.
